main event: A pilot observed a brilliantly lighted object flying at high altitude and high speed of approximately 700-800 mph in the Greenland area on November 25, 1951.
interesting points: The object maintained a constant course and speed.
The pilot was unable to intercept the object.
This was the fourth sighting in the past week in the same area.
The sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes before the object disappeared from view.
The report was received with a REG PRIORITY at 2230L on November 23, 1951.
